modules.description: Converts and manipulates time durations in nanoseconds, supporting arithmetic operations and unit conversions. It handles unsigned 64-bit integers and ensures valid input ranges. Used to validate and process time intervals in system monitoring and logging applications.

The module provides functions for converting durations between nanoseconds and various time units, including days, years, and floating-point representations, with precise handling of 64-bit unsigned integers. It supports both input conversions (e.g., from microseconds or seconds) and output conversions (e.g., to milliseconds or minutes), ensuring accuracy for large values up to 584 years. Use cases include high-precision time calculations in systems requiring strict unit consistency, such as scientific simulations or real-time scheduling.
